font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">more </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">than one QS will </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">be required</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">.  On the other hand</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">, where</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">numerous competent</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">operatives</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">are</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">carrying out electrical installation work </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">on </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">a large block of flats</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> or single housing development with repetitive work</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">, </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">only one QS may be necessary</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">. </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">The final decision will be made after reviewing the </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">objective evidence </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">available</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">.</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 72pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">The number of </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">QS</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> in a</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> company</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">is</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> currently</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> reviewed </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">annually </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">at each assessment and can be varied if any of </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">the conditions change</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">.</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">Listed below are examples of </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">electrical contracting firms</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> currently registered</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> with Certsure</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">, the </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">breadth </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">of their work and the number of QS they employ.</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="circle" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><ul type="circle" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Courier New'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 66.2pt; padding-left:5.8pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; text-decoration:underline">Firm A</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> – A typical micro enterprise issuing 412 notifications </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">per annum </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">with 1 QS and 1 employee</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Courier New'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 66.2pt; padding-left:5.8pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; text-decoration:underline">Firm B</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">– </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">A major national company issuing 24,</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">084 notifications per annum has 7 QS nationwide and </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">400 employ</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">ees including sub contractors.  </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">The company also employs a </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">contract</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">s manager, site agents and quantity surveyors, different roles all contributing to the overall management and supervision of their projects.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Courier New'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 66.2pt; padding-left:5.8pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; text-decoration:underline">Firm C</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">– </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">1</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">850 notifications per </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">annum with 2 QS operating out of one</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> office serving East Anglia and Gr</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">eater London with 80 employees.</span></li></ul></ul><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">The QS is required to have direct responsibility, on a day to day basis, for the safety, quality and technical standard of the </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">electrical </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">installation work carried out.</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">The QS is legally responsible for the work undertaken by those they supervise including whether they are competent to undertake the work.</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">The QS signs off the work as compliant with the requirements of the regulations and is responsible for notifying the work.</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">In conclusion w</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">e believe there is no objective evidence to suggest the QS system is not working and that to increase the costs and regulatory burden on electrical firms by insisting that all competent </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">persons </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">who may be currently undertaking work </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">under the </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">supervis</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">ion of</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">a QS</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> become registered is impractical</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">.</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">It </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">would be costly </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">and place additional burden on</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">the </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">industry and there is no evidence to suggest that a</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">n</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">additional </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">safety benefit would be delivered.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">The current framework provides the opportunity for continuous improvement</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> and our suggestion to the </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">Committee </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">is that the guidance criteria used for deciding the number of QS is enshrined in the</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> M</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">inimum </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">T</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">echnical </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">Competency</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> requirement</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">imposed on the scheme operators by DCLG</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">, ensuring </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">a </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">consistent application against agreed standards.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"